<p style="text-align: justify;">Though his first feature film was <strong>The Express </strong>(2008), he got recognition only in 2013 with his role as Jackie Robinson in the movie <strong>42</strong>. In the following year, he acted on <strong>Draft Day</strong> and <strong>Get on Up</strong>. His performance and acting skills were critically praised for his role as James Brown in <strong>Get on Up</strong>.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">Recently in 2016 he finally got the boost in his acting career that he had been waiting for by bagging the role of Tâ€™Challa/ Black Panther in the movie <strong>Captain America: Civil war</strong>, the first in a five picture deal with one of the biggest franchises <strong>Marvel</strong> for which he was widely admired worldwide. Moreover, he is set to reprise the role in the much awaited and talked about movie <strong>Black Panther</strong>Â which became one of the highest movies inÂ  2018. Additionally, he will be seen inÂ  <strong>Avengers: Infinity WarÂ </strong>reprising the same role.</p>
